# Translating the most needed phone_brand names from chinese to english

def translate_to_english(text, source_language):
    translation = translate(text, source_language, 'en')
    return translation

In [414]:
## Calculating the Variance explained and the cummulative variance explained
total = sum(eig_vals)
var_exp = [ (i/total)*100  for i in sorted(eig_vals,reverse=True)]
cum_var_exp = np.cumsum(var_exp)
print('Variance Explained: ',var_exp)
print('Cummulative Variance Explained: ',cum_var_exp)

Variance Explained:  [29.366547857579377, 26.657420213859755, 16.154622529996622, 14.511500569720633, 12.128076621232303, 0.7153915425595925, 0.4664406650517107]
Cummulative Variance Explained:  [ 29.36654786  56.02396807  72.1785906   86.69009117  98.81816779
  99.53355933 100.        ]
In [415]:
## Scree plot
plt.bar(range(7),var_exp, align='center',color='lightblue',edgecolor='black',label='Indiviual Explained Varinace')
plt.step(range(7), cum_var_exp, where='mid',color='red',label='Cummulative explained Variance')
plt.legend(loc = 'best')
plt.ylabel('Explained Variance Ratio')

  • We can see that approximately 100.0% of variance is explained by the first 5 variables.
  • so, we can choose the optimal number of principal components as 5.

4.2 K-means Clustering¶

cluster_range = range(1,15)
cluster_errors = []

for num_clusters in cluster_range:
   
    clusters = KMeans(num_clusters, n_init=10)
    clusters.fit(scaled_features_df)
    
    labels = clusters.labels_
    centroids = clusters.cluster_centers_
    
    cluster_errors.append(clusters.inertia_)

# Continue with further analysis using the sampled data and cluster labels

from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score

kmeans_score = []

for i in range(2,15):
    start_time = time.time()
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=i)
    kmeans = kmeans.fit(sampled_data)
    labels = kmeans.predict(sampled_data)
    elapsed_time = time.time() - start_time
    print(f" Elapsed time = {elapsed_time} seconds")
    print(i,silhouette_score(sampled_data,labels))
